Make sure to install the PHPSpreadsheet library and require the necessary files:

```shell
composer require phpoffice/phpspreadsheet
```

This code initializes the PHPSpreadsheet object, sets the active sheet, and defines the sheet title. It then sets values for cell A1, B1, and optionally C1. Finally, it uses the Xlsx writer to save the spreadsheet into a file named "your_file.xlsx".

In PHPSpreadsheet, the code to create a writer to save the spreadsheet as an Excel 2007 file (XLSX) is slightly different. Here's the equivalent code using PHPSpreadsheet:

```php
use PhpOffice\PhpSpreadsheet\IOFactory;

$writer = IOFactory::createWriter($spreadsheet, 'Xlsx');
$writer->save('your_file.xlsx');
```

Replace `$spreadsheet` with your instance of `Spreadsheet` object. This code creates a writer object using the `IOFactory` class and sets the writer type to `'Xlsx'` for Excel 2007 format. Then, it saves the spreadsheet to the file named "your_file.xlsx" using the writer's `save()` method.

